## Day 17/ 120

Today I learned about advanced analysis tools in Excel:
- Forecast Sheet  
- What-If Analysis  
- Scenarios  
- Goal Seek  

At first, they all felt similar. But as I practiced, I started noticing the differences.

Forecasting looks at past data to project trends forward.  
What-If and Scenarios help test different possibilities.  
Goal Seek works backwards — finding the input needed to reach a specific result.

It’s still a bit overwhelming, but it’s changing how I think about data. Not just reporting what happened, but exploring what could happen.

Still piecing it together.

